Eight vultures on the Israeli-occupied Golan Heights – about half the birds’ population there – have been poisoned to death, Israeli officials say. The bodies of the griffon vultures were found on Friday morning, the Israel Nature and Parks Authority said. It is not known what poison killed the birds or who was behind the attack. An investigation is under way. Officials had been trying to increase the vulture count after their numbers declined. Netanyahu threatens Syria with air strike over romance with Iran Hamas ‘seizes Israeli spy dolphin’ off Gaza Saudi Arabia condemns Trump’s recognition of Israeli claim on Golan Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin